a:r.a:t: Printer toner is expected to grow in the OEC, benefitting from the shift to laser based printing and effectiveness of MPS

Aftermarket color toner for printers is projected to grow by 6.4% through 2020F, driven by improved aftermarket manufacturing capabilities, growth in color usage and customer receptivity to aftermarket products
Katun’s strong relationship in the OEC channel and emerging leadership in the aftermarket color segment well position the Company to further penetrate the color printer toner market
Presently, the Company sells far more MFD toner than printer toner, representing a large opportunity with existing customers
Bringing existing customer printer to MFD sales ratios in line with the market would represent an additional $19.6 million in sales in 2016
OEC Color Toner Market for Printers
The market for OEC printer toner in NA is 1.4 times the market size of MFD toner. In EUR, the market for OEC
is 0.8 times the market size of MFD
however, actual Katun MFD toner sales are at a 2.9 ratio relative to actual printer, with printer under-indexed relative to market opportunity
Getting active customers that only buy printer or only buy MFD toner to buy in a ratio in line with the market
would result in an additional $4.4 million in sales in NA and $4.5 million in sales in EUR ($8.9 million total sales)
Getting active customers that buy both printer and MFD toner to buy in a ratio in line with the market
would result in an additional $7.8 million in sales in NA and $11.8 million in sales in EUR ($19.6 million total sales)
stands to realize enormous potential simply by bringing existing customers in line with the market
